==English==

===Pronunciation===
IPA: [[WEAE]] /pɛɹ.aɪˈdo.li.ə/  ([[Editing Rhymes:English:-əʊ.li.ə|rhymes]])

===Etymology===
para- (something wrong), and eidolon (a ghostly image or phantom)

===Noun===
The tendancy to interpret a vauge stimulus as something clear and distinct.  E.g. Early astronomers saw canals on Mars due to pareidolia; Pareidolia is what allows us to see pictures in clouds.

